10 must be adjusted with the association, but the insurance proceeds for that loss are payable to any
11 insurance trustee designated for that purpose, or otherwise to the association, and not to any
12 mortgagee or beneficiary under a deed of trust. The insurance trustee or the association shall hold
13 any insurance proceeds in trust for unit owners and lien holders as their interests may appear.
14 Subject to the provisions of subsection (h), the proceeds must be disbursed first for the repair or
15 restoration of the damaged property, and unit owners and lien holders are not entitled to receive
16 payment of any portion of the proceeds unless there is a surplus of proceeds after the property has
17 been completed, repaired or restored, or the condominium is terminated.
18 (f) An insurance policy issued to the association does not prevent a unit owner from
19 obtaining insurance for his or her own benefit.
20 (g) An insurer that has issued an insurance policy under this section shall issue certificates
21 or memoranda of insurance to the association and, upon written request, to any unit owner,
22 mortgagee, or beneficiary under a deed of trust. The insurer issuing the policy may not cancel or
23 refuse to renew it until thirty (30) days after notice of the proposed cancellation or nonrenewal has
24 been mailed to the association, each unit owner, and each mortgagee or beneficiary under a deed
25 of trust to whom a certificate or memorandum of insurance has been issued at their respective last
26 known addresses.
27 (h) Any portion of the condominium for which insurance is required under this section that
28 is damaged or destroyed shall be repaired or replaced promptly by the association unless: (1) The
29 condominium is terminated; (2) Repair or replacement would be illegal under any state or local
30 health or safety statute or ordinance; or (3) Eighty percent (80%) of the unit owners, including
31 every owner of a unit or assigned, limited common element that will not be rebuilt, vote not to
32 rebuild unless insurance proceeds are adequate to rebuild. The cost of repair or replacement in
33 excess of insurance proceeds, after the application of the association’s policy deductible, is a
34 common expense, unless the declaration provides or bylaws provide otherwise. If the entire
